你真的肯定？

174
00:12:16,93 --> 00:12:18,76
I'll call you back.
我再回你电话

175
00:12:29,44 --> 00:12:32,07
So we can be friends who sleep together.
我们可以当有性关系的朋友

176
00:12:32,65 --> 00:12:35,62
Absolutely. This'll just be something we do.
没错，这不代表什么

177
00:12:35,82 --> 00:12:38,51
Like racquetball.
就像打壁球一样

178
00:12:39,52 --> 00:12:41,85
Sounds smart and healthy to me.
我觉得聪明又健康

179
00:12:43,12 --> 00:12:47,19
So just out of curiosity...
不过基于好奇心

180
00:12:47,46 --> 00:12:51,02
...do you currently have any other "racquetball" buddies?
你还有几个打壁球的伙伴？

181
00:12:52,03 --> 00:12:54,19
Just your dad.
只有你爸爸一个

182
00:12:55,87 --> 00:12:58,46
Although that's actually racquetball.
虽然那是真的壁球

183
00:12:58,77 --> 00:13:02,14
You know,I do have a blind date...
我下星期二…

184
00:13:02,38 --> 00:13:05,61
...with my sister's neighbor next Tuesday.
要和我妹妹的邻居约会

185
00:13:08,35 --> 00:13:10,28
Do you want me to cancel it?
你希望我取消吗？

186
00:13:10,85 --> 00:13:12,28
No!
不要

187
00:13:15,46 --> 00:13:19,19
Because if you did, that means you'd be canceling for me.
如果你取消 那就是为我取消的

188
00:13:20,19 --> 00:13:22,82
-And we're just friends. -Exactly.
而我们只是朋友 没错

189
00:13:27,07 --> 00:13:28,86
Oh,don't sit down.
不要坐

190
00:13:29,07 --> 00:13:30,80
-Ready to go? -You bet.
可以走了吗？ 可以

191
00:13:31,04 --> 00:13:33,17
And first,here's a gift.
不过先送你一个礼物

192
00:13:37,68 --> 00:13:39,84
Stretchy pants?!
伸缩内裤？

193
00:13:40,25 --> 00:13:44,81
The greatest things in the world! If I were you,I'd wear them every day.
这个东西好得要命 如果是我，我会天天穿

194
00:13:46,65 --> 00:13:48,92
Gee,thank you. Really,that's so nice.
谢谢，真的，你太体帖了

195
00:13:49,19 --> 00:13:53,59
But,to be honest, I don't think I can wear these.
不过说老实话 我看我不能穿

196
00:13:53,86 --> 00:13:57,16
They're so tight. I'd feel like I'm on display.
太紧了，我会觉得 好像是给人家看的

197
00:13:59,07 --> 00:14:00,36
I'm sorry.
对不起

198
00:14:00,57 --> 00:14:02,76
That's all right. I'll figure....
没关系，我再想办法…

199
00:14:07,84 --> 00:14:08,67
How's it going?
大家好吗？

200
00:14:08,94 --> 00:14:10,27
Good.
很好

201
00:14:10,88 --> 00:14:12,24
How's The Shining?
“鬼店”好不好看？

202
00:14:12,45 --> 00:14:14,91
Danny just went into Room 217.
丹尼刚走进217号房

203
00:14:15,12 --> 00:14:18,85
The next part's the best! That dead lady in the bathtub
下面是最精彩的 浴缸里的死女人…

204
00:14:20,19 --> 00:14:21,45
You're gonna ruin it!
这样就不好看了

205
00:14:21,69 --> 00:14:23,75
I'll talk in code.
我用密码说

206
00:14:24,02 --> 00:14:27,52
Remember when the kid sees those two "blanks" in the hallway?
记得小孩在走廊 看到那两个“空白”吗？

207
00:14:28,46 --> 00:14:30,09
Yeah,that's very cool.
对，那里很好看

208
00:14:30,80 --> 00:14:34,79
All "blank" and no "blank" makes "blank" a "blank-blank."
所有的“空白”都把 “空白”弄成“空白”

209
00:14:36,94 --> 00:14:38,43
No,the end!
不，讲结局

210
00:14:38,64 --> 00:14:41,11
Jack almost kills them with the "blank"...
杰克差点用“空白” 杀了他们

211
00:14:41,31 --> 00:14:43,87
... but in the last second, they get away.
不过到最后关头 他们还是跑了

212
00:14:44,81 --> 00:14:46,91
I can't believe you just did that.
你居然做这种事

213
00:14:47,15 --> 00:14:49,91
I can't believe she cracked your code.
她居然识破你的密码

214
00:14:54,76 --> 00:14:58,28
Okay. Laurie proposes to Jo and she says no...
好，劳瑞跟乔求婚，她拒绝了

215
00:14:58,56 --> 00:15:02,93
...even though she's in love with him. Then he ends up marrying Amy.
虽然她其实爱着他 他后来娶了爱美

216
00:15:05,90 --> 00:15:08,33
Mine was by accident!
我不是存心要讲的

217
00:15:09,80 --> 00:15:13,33
The boiler explodes and destroys the hotel and kills the dad.
锅炉爆炸，烧毁旅馆 那个爸爸也被烧死了

218
00:15:15,58 --> 00:15:16,60
Beth dies.
贝丝死了

219
00:15:25,59 --> 00:15:28,11
Beth dies?
贝丝死了？

220
00:15:29,49 --> 00:15:33,32
Is that true? If I keep reading,is Beth gonna die?
真的吗？如果继续看下去 贝丝就会死？

221
00:15:33,69 --> 00:15:36,93
No,Beth doesn't die. She doesn't die. Does she,Rachel?
不，贝丝不会死，她不会死 对不对，瑞秋？

222
00:15:37,70 --> 00:15:39,33
He's asking if you've ruined...
他问的是你是不是破坏了

223
00:15:39,53 --> 00:15:42,97
...the first book he's ever loved that didn't star Jack Nicholson.
他喜欢的第一本不是由 杰克尼克逊当主角的小说？

224
00:15:46,77 --> 00:15:49,80
No. She doesn't die.
不，她不会死

225
00:15:50,01 --> 00:15:51,88
Then why would you say that?
那你干嘛这么说？

226
00:15:55,88 --> 00:15:59,55
Because I wanted to hurt you.
因为我故意要伤害你

227
00:16:01,49 --> 00:16:04,18
Oh,there they are. I dropped my keys.
在这里，我的钥匙掉了

228
00:16:06,96 --> 00:16:08,33
Got them.
找到了

229
00:16:15,34 --> 00:16:17,57
Sorry. I'm sorry.
对不起，对不起

230
00:16:17,84 --> 00:16:19,90
You would not believe my day.
你一定不敢相信我今天有多惨

231
00:16:20,31 --> 00:16:23,87
I had to work two shifts. And then to top it off...
我上了两个班 除此之外…

232
00:16:24,14 --> 00:16:28,31
... I lost one of my fake boobs in a grill fire.
我的义乳又被烤炉的火烧了

233
00:16:31,69 --> 00:16:33,18
What are you smiling at?
你在笑什么？

234
00:16:33,42 --> 00:16:35,68
I was thinking your day could still pick up.
我在想可能会柳暗花明又一村

235
00:16:44,06 --> 00:16:46,00
I love this "friend" thing!
我喜欢这种朋友关系

236
00:16:53,01 --> 00:16:57,21
Robert's gonna be here any second, so could one of you just tell him?
劳勃马上就要来了 你们哪个人跟他说好吗？

237
00:16:57,78 --> 00:16:58,90
Please,right now.
拜托，马上说

238
00:16:59,18 --> 00:17:03,08
Every time I see him,it's "ls it on the loose? Is it watching me?"
我一见他就想“那玩意儿 是不是晃来晃去看着我”

239
00:17:04,92 --> 00:17:05,94
We can't tell him.
我们不能跟他说

240
00:17:06,19 --> 00:17:11,28
You can't go up to a guy you barely know and talk about his "stuff."
你不能跟素昧平生的人 谈他的“那话儿”

241
00:17:11,76 --> 00:17:15,70
He's right. Even if it's to say something complimentary.
他说得对 就算是赞美也不行

242
00:17:20,80 --> 00:17:22,10
You ready for the gym?
可以去健身房了吗？

243
00:17:22,37 --> 00:17:25,30
There's a new rock-climbing wall. We can spot each other.
有一面新的攀岩墙 我们可以互相侦查

244
00:17:27,24 --> 00:17:29,71
Yeah,I can spot you from here.
我从这里就可以侦查你

245
00:17:32,95 --> 00:17:33,91
What?
什么？

246
00:17:35,78 --> 00:17:37,72
Listen,Robert....
听我说，劳勃

247
00:17:38,15 --> 00:17:39,31
Hey,don't we have to...?
我们不是要…

248
00:17:39,59 --> 00:17:41,14
Yeah,we got....
对，我们要

249
00:17:48,56 --> 00:17:51,12
I think you're really,really great.
我觉得你这个人真的很棒

250
00:17:51,77 --> 00:17:53,67
Oh,God. Here we go again.
老天，又来了

251
00:17:53,93 --> 00:17:58,39
Why does this keep happening? Is it something I'm putting out there?
为什么老是发生这种事？ 我什么东西让你不高兴？

252
00:18:00,67 --> 00:18:04,30
Is this my fault? Or am I just nuts?
这是我的错吗？

253
00:18:07,48 --> 00:18:09,95
I don't know what to say.
我不知道该怎么说

254
00:18:11,02 --> 00:18:15,98
Hey,buddy? This is a family place. Put the mouse back in the house.
老弟？这是阖家光临的地方 把老鼠放回屋里去

255
00:18:39,28 --> 00:18:43,05
Really? It's just like everyone else's apartment.
真的？这间公寓很普通啊

256
00:18:43,28 --> 00:18:45,48
It's got rooms and walls and ceilings.
一样有房间、墙壁和天花板

257
00:18:45,79 --> 00:18:48,95
I just wanted to see where you live. Now give me the tour.
我只是想看看你住的地方 带我参观参观

258
00:18:49,19 --> 00:18:50,85
Oh,my God!
我的天

259
00:18:51,16 --> 00:18:53,56
-This is the living room. -That's nice.
这里是客厅 真舒适

260
00:18:54,80 --> 00:18:57,29
-And this is the kitchen. -That's real pretty.
这里是厨房 真漂亮

261
00:18:57,53 --> 00:18:59,62
Wait a minute. Don't I get to see the bedroom?
等一下 我不能参观卧室吗？

262
00:19:00,67 --> 00:19:03,57
Well,it's pretty much your typical...
这是很普通的…

263
00:19:04,84 --> 00:19:06,31
... bedroom.
卧室

264
00:19:07,34 --> 00:19:11,14
We're still on this side of the door. I didn't get to see it.
我们还在门的这一头 我还没看到

265
00:19:11,38 --> 00:19:16,04
Oh,shoot. Maybe next time. Thanks for a lovely evening.
要命，下次吧 今晚非常愉快

266
00:19:33,93 --> 00:19:35,73
So who is she?
她是谁？

267
00:19:36,07 --> 00:19:39,06
That was the blind date I told you about.
我跟你说过 就是我妹妹介绍的人

268
00:19:39,27 --> 00:19:42,33
She called and switched it from Tuesday.
她打电话来改期到今天

269
00:19:44,18 --> 00:19:46,04
Did you like her?
你喜欢她吗？

270
00:19:46,25 --> 00:19:51,05
I'm just asking as a friend, because I am totally fine with this.
我是以朋友的身份问的 因为我不会不高兴

271
00:19:53,55 --> 00:19:55,35
Well,you seem fine.
你看起来很高兴

272
00:19:56,09 --> 00:19:59,18
Okay,you know what? I'm not fine. I'm not.
好，你知道吗？ 我不高兴，我很不高兴

273
00:19:59,43 --> 00:20:03,16
I mean,how could I be fine? Hearing you come in with her.
我怎么高兴得起来？ 听到你跟她进来

274
00:20:03,36 --> 00:20:05,85
She wants to see your bedroom.
她还想参观你的卧室

275
00:20:13,24 --> 00:20:14,73
You know what?
你知道吗？

276
00:20:17,08 --> 00:20:19,20
What if we're friends...
我们或许可以做朋友…

277
00:20:20,05 --> 00:20:21,98
...who don't see other people?
但不跟其他人交往

278
00:20:24,38 --> 00:20:25,85
You mean "exclusive" friends?
你是说“专属的”朋友？

279
00:20:26,69 --> 00:20:28,09
Why not?
有何不可？

280
00:20:28,99 --> 00:20:32,48
I mean,this has been the most amazing week.
我是说，这个星期美好极了

281
00:20:33,93 --> 00:20:35,69
Would it be so terrible?
这也没什么不好吧

282
00:20:36,60 --> 00:20:40,66
Even if we were friends who lived together?
我们还可以一面做朋友 一面住在一起

283
00:20:43,00 --> 00:20:47,50
Or maybe someday,friends who stood up in front of their other friends...
或许有一天 可以站在其他朋友面前

284
00:20:47,74 --> 00:20:50,44
...and vowed to be friends forever.
发誓当一辈子的朋友

285
00:20:57,28 --> 00:20:59,55
You know,we're back where we were.
我们又回到原点了

286
00:21:01,29 --> 00:21:06,42
Honey,I would love to do all that, but nothing's changed.
亲爱的，我求之不得 但一切都没有改变

287
00:21:06,76 --> 00:21:10,36
That's not true. You don't have a moustache.
不是这样的 你把胡子刮掉了

288
00:21:12,60 --> 00:21:15,09
Okay,one thing's changed.
好吧，有一件事改变了

289
00:21:15,54 --> 00:21:18,97
But we still want different things, and we know how this is gonna end.
但我们生活目标仍不同 我们都知道结局会怎么样

290
00:21:20,24 --> 00:21:21,71
You know what?
你知道吗？

291
00:21:22,21 --> 00:21:25,04
I gotta walk out of here right now.
我得马上离开这个房间

292
00:21:26,38 --> 00:21:30,25
Because getting over you is the hardest thing I have ever had to do.
因为忘记你是我一生中 最不容易的一件事

293
00:21:32,22 --> 00:21:34,15
I don't think I could do it again.
我想我再也做不到了

294
00:21:35,22 --> 00:21:36,75
I know I couldn't.
我知道我做不到

295
00:21:52,64 --> 00:21:55,07
How about one last game of racquetball?
再打最后一场壁球怎么样？

296
00:22:01,11 --> 00:22:03,17
Watch the thorns!
小心玫瑰刺

297
00:22:10,69 --> 00:22:11,62
What?
怎么了？

298
00:22:13,96 --> 00:22:15,79
Beth is really,really sick.
贝丝病得很重很重

299
00:22:21,17 --> 00:22:25,30
Jo's there,but I don't think there's anything she can do.
乔在陪她 但我想她也没办法

300
00:22:30,41 --> 00:22:32,84
You wanna put the book in the freezer?
你要把书放在冰库里吗？

301
00:00:00,00 --> 00:00:00,00


